                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_daǧytʼajlag" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>daǧytʼajlag</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>daǧitʼajlag</orth></form><sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>бедственный</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>disastrous</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>гиблый</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>ruinous</q></abv:tr></sense></sense><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>Mæxæ mæt æmæ Morat ba fæwuncæ fud daǧitʼajlagi rasug</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Махамат и Морат бывают погибельно пьяны</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>Mahamat and Morat happen to be drunk to death</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>286%l3%l</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>k˳yst daǧytʼajlagmæ ærtardta</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>довел работу до бедственного состояния</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>[he] brought work to a disastrous state</q></abv:tr></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Происхождение не ясно. Возможна связь с <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>daǧət-</w> <gloss><q>рассеивать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w/> <gloss><q>разбрасывать</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">The etymology is not clear. Probably, there is a connection with <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>daǧət-</w> <gloss><q>disperse</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w/> <gloss><q>scatter</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>